==English==
===Pronunciation===
*frāz, /freɪz/, /<tt>freIz</tt>/

===Etymology===
Latin, from Greek [[φράζειν]] (phrazein)

====Homophones====
*[[fray]]s

===Noun===
'''phrase''' (''plural'' '''[[phrases]]''')

#A short written or spoken expression.
#A group of two or more words, such as "around the clock", that express an idea but do not form a complete sentence.
#A small section of [[music]] in a larger piece.

====Synonyms====
*(''group of two or more words that express an idea but do not form a complete sentence''): [[expression]], [[figure of speech]], [[locution]]

